      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">A 2-year-old child named Mia was brought to the Pediatrician by her mother, who is concerned about her daughter&#39;s unusual behavior and developmental patterns. The mother reports that Mia frequently plays with cats and has a cry that is reminiscent of a cat&#39;s meow. Upon examination, the Pediatrician observes several notable features: a high-pitched, cat-like cry, developmental delays, hyperactivity, aggression, short attention span, and some distinct facial characteristics. Based on these findings, the Pediatrician suspects Cri du Chat syndrome.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Considering the typical manifestations of Cri du Chat syndrome, which of the following additional findings is most likely to be observed in Mia?</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2024/03/16/picture13_HbjKDvS.jpg\" style=\"height:419px; width:300px\" /></p>",
